strong cash flow from operating activities with $4.4 billion provided in 2002,
$3.9 billion in 2001 and $6.2 billion in 2000. earnings, adjusted for non-cash
items, continue to be the primary source of operating cash flow with over $4
billion provided in each of the last three years.
